author: rhuijben
msg: * subversion/libsvn_wc/old-and-busted.c
(svn_wc__atts_to_entry): Following up on r39428, reinstate setting the
repository uuid, but don't apply a modify flag.

author: stsp
msg: * subversion/libsvn_client/patch.c
(apply_one_patch): If renaming the patched result on top of the target
file fails, try copy+delete before giving up.

author: rhuijben
msg: * subversion/libsvn_wc/update_editor.c
(absent_file_or_dir): Following up on r39394, handle unversioned nodes in a
way that doesn't break the ra_dav_neon authz tests.

author: rhuijben
msg: Following up on r39427 and in the spirit of r37550, remove the flags for
updating a repository uuid via entry modify.
(We ignored the changes in WC-NG anyway).
* subversion/libsvn_wc/entries.c
(fold_entry): Don't check for SVN_WC__ENTRY_MODIFY_UUID.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/entries.h
(SVN_WC__ENTRY_MODIFY_UUID): Remove. Leave open marker.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/log.c
(log_do_modify_entry): Remove uuid support.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/old-and-busted.c
(svn_wc__loggy_entry_modify): Remove uuid support.

author: rhuijben
msg: * subversion/libsvn_wc/update_editor.c
(accumulate_entry_props): In WC-NG the repository root and UUID are the
primary keys for a repository. The repository doesn't have to
initialize this value, as it had to in WC-1.0.
